        "is_accepted": false,
        "last_activity_date": 1500978968,
        "creation_date": 1500975949,
        "body": "<p>You defined a bidirectional \"manytoone\" association, so it's develepoer's responsability to keep consistent both sides of the association (that is: loanRequest and loanItems).<\/p>\n\n<p>You should set the field  loanRequest of the Loanitem entity to point to \"right\" LoanRequest.\nDo you so in the addLoanItem  ?<\/p>\n\n<p>Beside, unless you really need to \"navigate\" from one entity to the other and backward I suggest you to use unidirectional association, they are far more manageable and less prone to errors like this.<\/p>\n\n<p>Anyway, @XtremeBaumer is right, constructor of LoanItem should be empty.<\/p>\n",
        "answer_id": 45299603,
        "question_id": 45297435,
        "last_edit_date": 1500978968
    }],
